Jeanci Konfeksiyon Tekstil Sanayi Ve
Ticaret AS, a Turkish clothing manufacturer, will expand its
Serbian operation with a 6 million euro ($7 million) jeans
factory, Beta  news agency  reported, citing co-owner.  Jeanci plans production for brands that include Cavalli,
Ferre and Versace and will increase workforce tenfold to 1,150
when it completes the plant in the southern city of Leskovac in
2014, the report quoted Aydogan Turkyilmaz as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
